{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d1a0501-0778-4046-8880-9881d3a69ad1","content":"With **MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0**, the switch is a one-line change in your project file (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n**Remove or flip the property:**\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n\n<!-- After — either remove the line entirely, or: -->\n<UseVSTest>false</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** in MSTest.Sdk 3.x, so removing `<UseVSTest>` entirely is sufficient.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n\n| Area | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Run tests | `dotnet test` | `dotnet test` (still works) or run the test exe directly |\n| CLI options | `--filter`, `--logger` etc. | `--filter`, `--report-trx`, etc. (slightly different syntax) |\n| `.runsettings` | Fully supported | Supported, but some adapters may differ |\n\n**After the change:**\n1. Rebuild: `dotnet build`\n2. Run tests: `dotnet test`\n3. If you relied on VSTest-specific logger syntax (e.g., `--logger trx`), switch to `--report-trx` instead.\n\nNo additional NuGet packages are needed — MSTest.Sdk handles the platform dependency automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1c4aa3fc-1147-4e88-8fa3-87d841060632","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project that uses MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nWith MSTest.Sdk, the switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform is straightforward:\n\n1. Remove or set `<UseVSTest>` to `false` (Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default in newer MSTest.Sdk versions)\n2. There may be some other considerations\n\nLet me give a clear, concise answer.","outputTokens":483,"requestId":"67E0:CA1D0:2A40694:2E8B6C2:69FD3493"},"id":"78c45f09-c007-4ecd-9048-dd257d493326","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:55:59.419Z","parentId":"9322becb-ff49-4d66-a00c-ee2f5bd02a6a"}
